We do not have a President elect until the electors meet and choose a person to be the next president. It matters not what the news media states or wants to claim. It matters not if a person concedes or not. The people indirectly elect a President.

The people do not elect a President the people select a person they think should be the President, the electors elect the President.

Once the electors have cast their vote and said person hits 270 electoral votes cast that person shall become President Elect. 

This is our constitutional design like it or not. This is not to say that Joe Biden does not become President Elect it means he is not President Elect until decided on December 14th 2020.

Faithless electors are allowed and it does happen. Never has it changed the outcome of the people's selection.

MONTH OF OUR LADY OF SORROWS 

The Church dedicates the month of September to Our Lady of Sorrows. This devotion recalls the Blessed Virgin Marys spiritual martyrdom in virtue of her perfect union with the Passion of Christ. This was her role in salvation history, and what merited her place as the spiritual Mother of all Christians. This is symbolized by a single sword, or seven swords, piercing Mary's suffering heart, as foretold in Simeon's prophecy. Traditionally the Church meditates on the "Seven Sorrows" of our Blessed Mother: the prophecy of Simeon; the Holy Family's flight into Egypt; the loss of the Child Jesus for three days; the meeting of Mary and Jesus as he carried his cross; Jesus' crucifixion and death; Jesus' sacred body taken down from the cross; and Jesus' burial. The feast of Our Lady of Sorrows is September 15th.

When three tea ships, the Dartmouth, the Eleanor, and the Beaver, arrived in Boston Harbor, the colonists demanded that the tea be returned to England. After Massachusetts Governor Thomas Hutchinson refused, Patriot leader Samuel Adams organized the "tea party" with about 60 members of the Sons of Liberty. The British tea dumped in Boston Harbor on the night of December 16 was valued at some $18,000.

Parliament, outraged by the blatant destruction of British property, enacted the Coercive Acts, also known as the Intolerable Acts, in 1774. The Coercive Acts closed Boston to merchant shipping, established formal British military rule in Massachusetts, made British officials immune to criminal prosecution in America, and required colonists to quarter British troops. The colonists subsequently called the first Continental Congress to consider a united American resistance to the British.

Dev update.

Thanks to the lessons learned in the last stresstest, planet generation has been completely overhauled.

Worlds used to be pregenerated, 100 in the hierarchy to be exact, which took upward of 15 seconds to load the scene.

Now, a World is comprised of an array of biomes. When the planet needs to load, it first looks in a pool of pre-instantiated biomes to recycle. If none are available, it will spawn the gaps in the assembly.

This brings scene loadtime back under 1 second, with recycled biomes saving on garbage collection, and World assembly being controlled over the course of several frames; like a co-routine, only with the added side-effect of seeing the biome assembly in realtime.

Back to the day job, but looking forward to my next day off when I can try out this same process for ship hull crafting.

Thanks for listening!
